{{Otheruses|Treidum}}
'''Treidum''' was a [[Freighter/Legends|freighter]] owner who was a subscriber to, and commenter on, [[Cynabar's Droid Datalog]]. In [[1 BBY/Legends|1 BBY]], Treidum ran a load of [[Roche Hive Mechanical Apparatus Design and Construction Activity for Those Who Need the Hive's Machines/Legends|Roche]] [[Siak-series protocol droid|Siak Protocol Droids]] to the planet [[Derilyn]] in the [[Elrood sector/Legends|Elrood sector]]. There, the smuggler was jumped by [[Pirate/Legends|pirates]], most likely the [[Khuiumin Survivors]] who [[Platt Okeefe/Legends|Platt Okeefe]] later warned were operating in the area. Treidum survived the pirate attack, and on returning to [[Berchest/Legends|Berchest]], posted a warning to other smugglers about the area. The warning was included in the next version of [[Cynabar's Droid Datalog]].<ref name="CFTD">''[[Cynabar's Fantastic Technology: Droids]]''</ref>

Several [[Standard month/Legends|months]] later, Treidum commented on the entry for the [[WED15-D3]], stating that they had retrofitted their [[WED Treadwell repair droid/Legends|Treadwell]] droid with a repair database and six more [[Manipulator arm/Legends|manipulator arms]]. The modifications allowed the droid to repair Treidum's freighter faster.<ref name="CDD">{{JournalCite|14|Cynabar's Droid Datalog (article series)}}</ref>

